content.subject: Rick Webster
content.assertion: Rick introduced peer coaching principles - presume competence, ask questions not advice
content.quoted_text: Presume competence... We don't want to just be giving the advice of, if I were in your shoes, I would do such and such. We all know that doesn't work.

content.subject: Lizzy Summers
content.assertion: Lizzy presented her art business dilemma - multiple product lines and struggling with focus
content.quoted_text: Every product I have, every step I get, there's a thousand other steps I need to do.

content.subject: Lizzy Summers
content.assertion: Lizzy described her groundhog day feeling with projects
content.quoted_text: I'm at this impasse. This happens over and over and over. It's my groundhog nightmare.

content.subject: Jasmine Mahmoud
content.assertion: Jasmine presented her masking framework - masking is trying to eliminate error in advance
content.quoted_text: Masking is basically trying to eliminate error in advance. You're pre-editing everything, hiding anything risky, aiming for zero misunderstanding.

content.subject: Doug Snyder
content.assertion: Doug completed annual performance appraisal - two weeks late but done, treated it differently this time

content.subject: Gio
content.assertion: Gio found what lights her up - stayed up all night making music in GarageBand
content.quoted_text: stayed up all night making music

content.subject: Stara Shakti
content.assertion: Stara committed to using a paper planner and keeping it open on desk

content.subject: Stara Shakti
content.assertion: Stara praised the presume competence principle
content.quoted_text: I really love what you said about presuming competence. Even if it's not there right now, that person will get there.

content.subject: Jasmine Mahmoud
content.assertion: Jasmine shared she got 4000 views on her TikTok video about masking

content.subject: Rick Webster
content.assertion: Rick said you don't know what's behind someone's smile - people are struggling with things we might not know about
content.quoted_text: You don't know what's behind someone's smile. People are struggling with things that we might not know about.
